
****Setup Backend (Node.js + Express + MongoDB)*****

1.Create a folder backend

2.Open terminal inside backend

3.Run: 
          npm init -y
          npm install express mongoose cors body-parser
4.Create server.js
          &write  down the code
5. Run backend
        node server.js in terminal
******MongoDB Atlas Cluster******
1.Go: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas

2.Sign up / Login

3.Click Build a Cluster → Free Tier (M0) → choose cloud & region → Create Cluster

4.Add DB User: Database Access → Add User
           Username: xxxx(any)

           Password: xxxx(any)

           Role: Read and Write any DB
5.Whitelist IP: Network Access → Add IP Address → 0.0.0.0/0 (for testing)

6.Get Connection URI: Clusters → Connect → Connect your application(copy pastr the url & add created username and password)

7.Database & collection auto-create when first document is inserted

/////////////create database in using before used cluster////////////////

              1.Go to your cluster → click Collections

              2.Click Create Database

              3.Enter:

                       Database Name: xxx

                       Collection Name: xxx

                       Click Create

             4.This is optional because method A auto-creates everything.

*****Setup Frontend (React)*********
1.Create React app
     npx create-react-app frontend
     cd frontend
2.Replace src/App.js
3.Replace src/App.css
4.Run frontend
      npm start


